Lapidras is a home-brew OS made by Sebastian Lund.
It is mainly programmed by learning purposes, and a bit of fun as well.

No copyright whatsoever here...

Current support is multithreading covering up to different priorities.
0  -  Here runs the GUI threads, as well as any other critical threads
1  -  Here runs the text-ui threads, as well as any other thread waiting for user input
2  -  Regular applications run here, and share equally of the processor user preemptive switching
	
I really don't want to write all this, as I cba to do so..
